properties.Name: Lien
properties.Description:
A lien is a legal claim that attaches property in which a creditor who holds the lien can have the property sold to satisfy the lien.

A lien is merely a claim until it is enforced legally, which means the lien holder has to take actions to make it occur.  

However, the simple presence of a lien can have an effect on the credit-worthiness of a party because it is a potentially serious financial liability.

In practical terms, a lien places the legal title of the attached property in doubt and makes the sale of that property difficult or impossible.

Liens also compete with UCC security interests, which is a security interest in personal property put up as collateral.
